JOHANNESBURG - Four children are receiving trauma counselling after being abducted from a Johannesburg orphanage. Police are searching for six armed men, who hijacked an ambulance and drove to the children's home in Eikenhof on Wednesday night. The suspects had disguised themselves as emergency personnel. They forced two guards and some of the children, who were playing outside, into the vehicle Fortunately, police intervened in time after noticing the ambulance was being driven recklessly. They tried to stop the vehicle but a shoot-out ensued. The suspects then abandoned the vehicle and fled. The orphanage cares for 60 children -- and this is not the first time it's been targeted. * Malungelo Booi has the full story - watch his video report in the gallery above. eNCA